Sentence, Clause, and Complex Sentences:
a sentence can also be a clause and in such a situation we call it an independent clause.
A sentence has a subordinate clause, as well.
when two sentences are connected with a comma, connector or conjunctions like and or etc, in such a situation, we call a sentence a compound sentence.
And when a sentence has another subordinate clause in it, then we call that sentence a complex sentence.

